MATHLIB Function Reference

Double Precision

This section provides a description of the functions that are double precision.

Double Precision Functions

The routines included in the Math library are provided as both single- and double-precision versions. DP is used to identify the double-precision functions.

  • Acosdp
  • Acoshdp
  • Asindp
  • Asinhdp
  • Atan2dp
  • Atandp
  • Cosdp
  • Coshdp
  • Divdp
  • Exp10dp
  • Exp2dp
  • Expdp
  • Log10dp
  • Log2dp
  • Logdp
  • Powdp
  • Recipdp
  • Rsqrtdp
  • Sindp
  • Sinhdp
  • Sqrtdp
  • Tandp
  • Tanhdp
